         id="starting-debugging-tests-from-the-command-line">
   <title>Starting Debugging Tests From the Command Line</title>
   <description>TODO: Add description.</description>
   <introduction>
      <ordered-list>
         <list-item>
            <paragraph>Set some breakpoints in your test code</paragraph>
         </list-item>
         <list-item>
            <paragraph>./gradlew connectedInstrumentTest</paragraph>
         </list-item>
         <list-item>
            <paragraph>In Android Studio, go to Run / Attach Debugger to running process</paragraph>
         </list-item>
         <list-item>
            <paragraph>Wait until you see your test process, since it might take a few seconds</paragraph>
         </list-item>
         <list-item>
            <paragraph>Choose it in the "Choose Process" window (it will look something like <external-ref href="http://cl.ly/image/0v313G320T3B">this</external-ref>)</paragraph>
         </list-item>
         <list-item>
            <paragraph>Wait until it reaches your breakpoint</paragraph>
         </list-item>
      </ordered-list>
   </introduction>
</article>
